    h1.bd-title#content Typography
    p.bd-lead Documentation and examples for Bootstrap typography, including global settings, headings, body text, lists, and more.

    h2#global-settings Global settings
    p
        | Bootstrap sets basic global display, typography, and link styles. When more control is needed, check out the 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/text/') textual utility classes
        | .
    ul
        li
            | Use a 
            a(href='/docs/content/reboot/#native-font-stack') native font stack
            |  that selects the best 
            code.highlighter-rouge font-family
            |  for each OS and device.
        li
            | For a more inclusive and accessible type scale, we assume the browser default root 
            code.highlighter-rouge font-size
            |  (typically 16px) so visitors can customize their browser defaults as needed.
        li
            | Use the 
            code.highlighter-rouge $font-family-base
            | , 
            code.highlighter-rouge $font-size-base
            | , and 
            code.highlighter-rouge $line-height-base
            |  attributes as our typographic base applied to the 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
            | .
        li
            | Set the global link color via 
            code.highlighter-rouge $link-color
            |  and apply link underlines only on 
            code.highlighter-rouge :hover
            | .
        li
            | Use 
            code.highlighter-rouge $body-bg
            |  to set a 
            code.highlighter-rouge background-color
            |  on the 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lg;body&gt;
            |  (
            code.highlighter-rouge #fff
            |  by default).
    p
        | These styles can be found within 
        code.highlighter-rouge _reboot.scss
        | , and the global variables are defined in 
        code.highlighter-rouge _variables.scss
        | . Make sure to set 
        code.highlighter-rouge $font-size-base
        |  in 
        code.highlighter-rouge rem
        | .
