    h2#responsive-typography Responsive typography
    p
        em Responsive typography
        |  refers to scaling text and components by simply adjusting the root element’s 
        code.highlighter-rouge font-size
        |  within a series of media queries. Bootstrap doesn’t do this for you, but it’s fairly easy to add if you need it.
    p
        | Here’s an example of it in practice. Choose whatever 
        code.highlighter-rouge font-size
        | s and media queries you wish.
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                html {
                    font-size: 1rem;
                }

                @include media-breakpoint-up(sm) {
                    html {
                        font-size: 1.2rem;
                    }
                }

                @include media-breakpoint-up(md) {
                    html {
                        font-size: 1.4rem;
                    }
                }

                @include media-breakpoint-up(lg) {
                    html {
                        font-size: 1.6rem;
                    }
                }